Ticket #001 – Outlook cannot sync inbox

User: Marketing
Issue: Outlook shows “Disconnected” and emails don’t update.
Cause: Wrong cached profile after password change.
Resolution:

Removed old Outlook profile

Created new profile via Control Panel → Mail

Forced autodiscover, updated credentials

Outlook re-synced successfully
Prevention: Add password-change checklist to onboarding guide.

Ticket #002 – Wi-Fi drops every few minutes

User: Warehouse
Issue: Connection unstable on Windows laptop.
Cause: Power saving mode turning off WLAN adapter.
Resolution:

Device Manager → WLAN adapter

Disabled “Allow computer to turn off device to save power”

Updated WLAN drivers

Verified stable connection for 20 minutes
Prevention: Add policy to disable WLAN power-saving on all warehouse devices.

Ticket #003 – Network printer offline

User: Accounting
Issue: Printer not reachable from any PC.
Cause: Printer got a new IP after DHCP refresh.
Resolution:

Checked printer panel → new IP found

Updated printer port in Windows

Restarted spooler

Test page successful
Prevention: Assign static IP for shared printers.

Ticket #004 – VPN cannot connect

User: Remote employee
Issue: VPN client stuck on “Negotiating…”
Cause: Certificate not installed after Windows update.
Resolution:

Re-installed VPN certificate

Cleared adapter configuration

Rebooted system

VPN connected normally
Prevention: Add certificate check to remote update script.

Ticket #005 – Teams microphone not detected

User: HR
Issue: User can hear calls but cannot speak.
Cause: Windows privacy settings blocking microphone.
Resolution:

Settings → Privacy → Microphone

Enabled “Allow apps to access microphone”

Restarted Teams

Test call confirmed working audio
Prevention: Add a quick audio-check guide for new laptops.

Ticket #006 – Slow PC after login

User: Sales
Issue: Laptop extremely slow for 5–10 minutes after boot.
Cause: OneDrive set to sync entire company SharePoint.
Resolution:

Limited sync to selected folders

Cleared OneDrive cache

Restarted laptop

Logon time dropped from 8 minutes to 1 minute
Prevention: Provide standard folder template for OneDrive.

Ticket #007 – Monitor not detected

User: Reception
Issue: Second monitor stays black.
Cause: HDMI cable damaged.
Resolution:

Tested monitor with another device

Replaced cable

Updated display drivers

Both screens detected
Prevention: Keep spare cables in IT storage.

Ticket #008 – Unable to print to PDF

User: Finance
Issue: “Print to PDF” missing from Windows printer list.
Cause: Windows feature removed after update.
Resolution:

Installed “Microsoft Print to PDF” under Optional Features

Restarted spooler

PDF output working
Prevention: Validate Windows features after major updates.

Ticket #009 – Locked out of Active Directory

User: New employee
Issue: Account locked after multiple failed logins.
Cause: Old credentials stored on mobile Outlook app.
Resolution:

Unlocked AD account

Removed old credentials from phone

Reconfigured Outlook with new password

Login stable
Prevention: Add “update mobile apps” step to onboarding.

Ticket #010 – Website not loading (internal tool)

User: Logistics
Issue: Internal tool unreachable; network error.
Cause: DNS cache corruption on Windows client.
Resolution:

Ran ipconfig /flushdns

Renewed IP

Verified host reachable

Page loaded normally
Prevention: Add DNS flush command to shortcut folder on shared drive.
